{# Template: kata-improvement/kata-improvement-convergence-check.j2 #}
{# goal: Compute normalized convergence metric for kata-improvement cycles. #}
{#
  Group: F (Kata & Coaching — CNS-grounded)
  Convergence method: LLM-assessed PDCA coherence with CNS counter awareness
  Measures: Whether the improvement kata's four steps produce a coherent,
    testable experiment. Specifically:
    1. Current condition is grounded in data (not assumption)
    2. Target condition is measurable and challenging
    3. Gap between current and target is clearly framed
    4. Next experiment is specific, testable, and addresses ONE obstacle
    5. Feedback timing is defined (Q5: "how quickly can we see?")
  Threshold: {{ _convergence.threshold }} — converged when metric ≤ threshold
  Improvement: (baseline - current) / baseline ≥ {{ _convergence.improvement_target | default(0.10) }}
  CNS integration: KataEngine captures metric_before/metric_after from CNS counters
    (kata.practices.completed, kata.automaticity.score). These are available
